  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: 2021.08.2-alpha\r\n\r\nOS & Version: All\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nThere's been some movement to standardize the parameters for the `block_count` argument for the `eth_feeHistory` RPC method. The spec says that clients should accept a hexstring representation of the block count, but currently Erigon only accepts integers.\r\n\r\nSee issues: https://github.com/ethereum/eth1.0-apis/issues/20, and https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/pull/23239\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\nn/a\r\n",
